        ],
        [
          "MOOC",
          "Online Learning",
          "Collaborative Filtering",
          "Next Course to Take",
          "28197 learners",
          "856 courses",
          "LMS logs, Course metadata, Responses for Cognitive Diagnosis, Knowledge Topics, ",
          "– MIRT static fit: estimate initial learner capacity uᵢ₀ and course difficulty dⱼ via maximum likelihood on ideal response qᵢⱼ\n\n\n– Implicit response pᵢⱼ computed as geometric mean of completion ratio aᵢⱼ and relative duration tᵢⱼ/ Dⱼ\n",
          "– After each new interaction aᵢⱼ, update learner capacity uᵢ,ₜ by Δuᵢ = pᵢ,ₜ·λᵢ·ReLU(dⱼ – uᵢ,ₜ₋₁) (Eq 4), where λᵢ is per-learner growth rate\n\n– Form embeddings: lᵢ,ₜ = concat(g(uᵢ,ₜ₋₁), l′ᵢ), cⱼ = concat(g(dⱼ), c′ⱼ), then predict with NCF or GRU by optimizing cross-entropy loss\n\n",
          "– Online setting: no offline train/test split for model fitting.– Compute pᵢⱼ via Eq 2; filter out records with missing aᵢⱼ or unknown",
          "Top-K courses (K=10)",
          "{Precision@10: 0.0715 - CT-E NCF, Precision@20: 0.1149 - CT-E NCF, Precision@40: 0.1827 - CT-E NCF, Hit_Ratio@10: 0.1605 - CT-E NCF, Hit_Ratio@20: 0.1290 - CT-E NCF, Hit_Ratio@40: 0.1025 - CT-E NCF}",
          "– Combines explainable MIRT capacities with CF.\n\n– CT-E NCF yields highest Precision & Hit gains over all baselines.\n\n– Capacity tracing correlates strongly with static MIRT estimates (ρ ≈ 0.79–0.99)",
          "- No user study; offline only.\n- Static dⱼ (no difficulty update).\n- Assumes weak interactions suffice for pᵢⱼ.\n- No specialized cold-start beyond MIRT init.\n\n- Assumes completion ≈ mastery (may misestimate short sessions).\n\n- No modeling of temporal drift beyond immediate updates."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
